name: integer_u32_byte_order
description: |
  Every byte in this u32 value is distinct. The little-endian encoding is
  therefore visibly ordered and catches whole-value byte reversal, swapped
  16/32/64-bit words, partial loads, and accidental truncation.
format: hex
decode-as: u32
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "unsigned-integer"
  - "u32"
  - "endianness"
  - "byte-order"
  - "word-order"
  - "truncation"
  - "canary"
---
04 03 02 01 # 0x01020304
